# 🚀 Kubernetes Troubleshooting — Fresher's Quick Reference

> **CloudDevOpsHub** | For Demo & Interview Prep | Batch 43

---

## 🔍 Golden Rule — Always Start Here

```bash
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>          # See what's wrong
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>          # Why it's wrong
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous       # What crashed
```

---

## 1. 🔴 Pod Not Starting
```bash
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
kubectl get events -n <namespace> --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'
```

---

## 2. 🌐 Service Not Accessible
```bash
kubectl get svc -n <namespace>
kubectl get endpoints <service-name> -n <namespace>   # Empty = label mismatch!
kubectl port-forward svc/<service-name> 8080:80        # Quick local test
```

---

## 3. 💾 PVC Not Bound
```bash
kubectl get pvc -n <namespace>
kubectl get pv
kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 4. ⚙️ ConfigMap Key Missing
```bash
kubectl get configmap -n <namespace>
kubectl describe configmap <cm-name> -n <namespace>
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- env | grep <KEY>        # Check inside pod
```

---

## 5. 🔁 CrashLoopBackOff
```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous        # ← Most important command!
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>           # Check liveness probe
```

---

## 6. 🖼️ ImagePullBackOff
```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>           # Check image name & tag
kubectl get secret -n <namespace>         # Check pull secret exists
```

---

## 7. 🖥️ Node Not Ready
```bash
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node-name>         # Check conditions
kubectl top node                          # CPU / Memory usage
```

---

## 8. ⏳ Pod Stuck in Pending (Scheduling Failed)
```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>           # Look at Events section
kubectl get nodes --show-labels           # Check nodeSelector match
```

---

## 9. 🔐 RBAC Forbidden Error
```bash
kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<sa>
kubectl get rolebindings -n <namespace>
```

---

## 10. 🌍 Ingress Not Working
```bash
kubectl get ingress -n <namespace>
kubectl describe ingress <name> -n <namespace>   # Check backend & rules
kubectl get ingressclass                          # Is controller set?
```

---

## ⚡ 5 Commands Every Fresher Must Know

```bash
kubectl get pods -A                        # All pods all namespaces
kubectl describe pod <name>                # Full detail + events
kubectl logs <name> --previous             # Crash logs
kubectl get events --sort-by=lastTimestamp # Timeline of what happened
kubectl rollout restart deployment/<name>  # Quick fix restart
```

---

> 💡 **Demo Tip:** In interviews, always say —  
> *"First I check pod status → then describe → then logs"*  
> That's the 3-step debug flow interviewers love! ✅

